{{Unreferenced|date=December 2008}} {{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}} {{Infobox company | name = Columbus Tubi | logo = Columbus Tubi logo.svg | logo_size = 230px | caption = | type = | traded_as = | genre = | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = 1919 | founder = Angelo Luigi Colombo | defunct = | location_city = [[Settala]] | location_country = Italy | location = | locations = | area_served = Worldwide | key_people = | industry = | products = | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | aum = <!-- Only used with financial services companies --> | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = {{URL|columbustubi.com}} | footnotes = | intl = }} '''Columbus Tubi''' is a manufacturer of steel tubing used in [[bicycle frame]]s, located in [[Settala]], in the [[Province of Milan]]. The company was founded in 1919 by A.L. Colombo and was taken over by Colombo's youngest son, Antonio, in 1977. It is now a division of Gruppo SPA, which also owns the bicycle manufacturer [[Cinelli]].
Columbus tubing was the main competitor to [[Reynolds Technology|TI Reynolds 531]] in the bicycle tube set market with many of the big name Italian manufacturers of bicycles and framesets utilising their products. Famous name builders such as [[Bianchi Bicycles|Bianchi]], [[Centurion (bicycle)|Centurion Bicycles]] (after 1981), [[De Rosa (bicycles)|De Rosa]], [[Ciocc]], [[Pinarello]] and [[Colnago]] all specified the Columbus tubesets as part of their range.
