{{Infobox Politician (general) |name = José J. Benítez Díaz |image = |caption = |state_senate= Puerto Rico |district = [[Puerto Rico Senatorial district VII|Humacao]] |term_start = 1917 |term_end = 1924 |predecessor = |successor = |order2 = |office2 = |governor2 = |term2 = |preceded2 = |succeeded2 = |party2 = |birth_date = November 24, 1866 {{cn|date=May 2018}} |birth_place = [[Luquillo, Puerto Rico]] |death_date = August 25, 1947 |death_place = |spouse = |children = |alma_mater = |profession = [[Politician]], Entrepreneur |party = [[Union of Puerto Rico]] |religion = |website = }} '''José Juan Benítez Díaz''' (c. 1866{{cn|date=May 2018}} &ndash; 1947<ref>aged 40 in 1907 when he served on the jury which convicted Panchito Dones{{cn|date=May 2018}}</ref>) was a [[Puerto Rican people|Puerto Rican]] businessman, entrepreneur and [[Unionista]] [[politician]]. He served as a member of the [[Senate of Puerto Rico]] from 1917 to 1924.
In 1917, Benítez Díaz was elected to the [[1st Puerto Rican Senate|first Senate of Puerto Rico]] for the [[Union of Puerto Rico]] party, representing the [[Puerto Rico Senatorial district VII|District of Humacao]]. He served in that position until 1924.
After that, Benítez was the owner of Benítez Sugar Company in [[Vieques, Puerto Rico|Vieques]].<ref>[https://archive.is/20120919183628/http://www.vieques1910-1950.com/resenas Militarismo y clases sociales en Vieques, 1910-1950]</ref>
